			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Playing damage song in Bazaar = violation of CoC<a name="53145"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 21 04 10:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=46&amp;ForumID=132">My Guide to AFK Training</a>
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"><u>The Myth:  You Have to Hit Something with Your Song:</u>
<br />

<br />
Buff songs, like Selos, give you an Icon in your Buff Window, and “Your feet move faster“ or some other message in your chat window.  You KNOW that the song is running.  When you sing DDD or Fear Song, your song icons will go grey, but unless you hit something, you won't get the “An Angry Mob Winces“ message.  You also don't get a buff icon, because it isn't a buff.  If you started the song with the Instrument equipped, and you did not miss a note, your song is going.  Look at your Song Gems, they will be grey, not brightly colored like they are when you are not singing.
<br />

<br />
No, you do NOT have to hit anyone with your DDD or Fear song to get Brass skill ups.  As I said, back in the day, we HAD to go somewhere where no one was to do it.  <b>Please do NOT AFK train your Brass skill in places where lots of Players go, (like Bazaar, or near the Bank or Nexus stone in PoK).  If you do that, people will get nasty red spam in their chat window saying “ButtMunch attempts to cast a spell on you, but you are protected!”.  This is very impolite, so please don't do that.  Find an quiet corner of PoK somewhere, equip your Brass Instrument, and sing the song</b>.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
As you can see, the eqdiva community does NOT condone being an asshat in any form, including spamming people in bazaar.
<br />

<br />
The next person who tells you that eqdiva said it's ok, tell them to send Firiona.Scherzo a tell so Klapton can straighten their n00b a$ out.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
