			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Reference Material<a name="53292"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 22 04 5:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Under Bard Info &gt;&gt; Guide &gt;&gt; AFK Training Instrument Skills
<br />

<br />
Within that Guide, find:
<br />

<br />
&quot;AFK Training:
<br />
It is quite simple, really.  Equip the correct Instrument for the song, start the song, go AFK (Away from Keyboard):  go to bed, watch TV, whatever.  I recommend AFK training all your Instrument Skills to your maximum level cap each time you ding.  Obivously you need to be somewhere safe to do this.  Plane of Knowledge, <b>Bazaar (YES! you can start a song going BEFORE you start Trader mode, and AFK train while you sell your junk!)</b>, Nexus, friendly cities, newbie zones near guards etc.
<br />

<br />
Speaking of safe...  <b>Level 18 Dennon's Disruptive Dischord (DDD) is an Area of Effect Damage/Debuff song!  Uh oh.  Ok, so the PoD lift in Gfay is not such a good idea anymore!  Where do you go?</b>
<br />

<br />
PoK, <b>Bazaar</b>, Nexus are all non-aggro zones.  In other words, if you hit a guard or merchant with your nasty song, they will not kill you.  In fact, they don't seem to even notice, hehe.  You can also find an out-of-the-way spot like climbing up a zone wall somewhere.  (That's what we did back in the day, before those zones I mentioned existed, hehe.)&quot;
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
This Guide is found under Bard Basics and I know many young bards read these guides for good information and tips.  I recommend adding a warning to this post about the bazaar AFK training in that you could get in trouble.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely,
<br />
Ashlii</span></td>
